386→                        <div id="content">Let $t(n)$ be maximal such that there is a representation\[n!=a_1\cdots a_n\]with $t(n)=a_1\leq \cdots \leq a_n$. Obtain good bounds for $t(n)/n$. In particular, is it true that\[\lim \frac{t(n)}{n}=\frac{1}{e}?\]Furthermore, does there exist some constant $c&#62;0$ such that\[\frac{t(n)}{n} \leq \frac{1}{e}-\frac{c}{\log n}\]for infinitely many $n$?</div>
387→                        <div id="problem_id"><a href="/391">#391</a>: <a href="#cite-ErGr80-391" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('ErGr80','391'); return false;">[ErGr80,p.75]</a><a href="#cite-Er96b-391" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('Er96b','391'); return false;">[Er96b]</a></div>
